item.description:

[quote=“Haiku01, post:1, topic:42713”]Problem!

[code]client.java:16888: cannot find symbol
symbol: method NewObjects()
location: class client
public boolean process() { writePlayers(); NewObjects(); // is being called regularily every 500ms

1 error
press any key to continue…[/code][br][size=1]Posted on: January 02, 2007, 07:14:33 AM[/size][hr]please help!

If your solution works you get admin![/quote]
Did you make a void called NewObjects?
search for something like this: “public void”
And put this OUTSIDE of a void:

public void NewObjects() { }
and inside the tags("{“and”}") put the new objects you want to make.
like makeGlobalObject(Xcoordinate,Ycoordinate,objectID,rotation,height)
at the first two, put the coordinates, for example 3426,2684
the third is the ID of the object, for example 11616(wooden door),
the rotation can be: 0,1,2,3 (0=WEST 1=NORTH(i think) 2=EAST 3=SOUTH) (if i’m right)
the height can be: 0(walls) 10(Normal) 12(wall objects) and so on…

hope i could help:)
